{"word":"G5389 - φιλοτιμέομαι - philotiméomai - fil-ot-im-eh'-om-ahee - Labour","sections":[{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">φιλοτιμέομαι</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong><span class=\"transliteration\">philotiméomai</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong><span class=\"phonetic\">fil-ot-im-eh'-om-ahee</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong><span class=\"short-definition\">Labour</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>இலக்கண சொல்வகை / Part(s) of speech: </strong>Verb / வினைச்சொல்</span>"},{"paragraph":"வினைச்சொல் - நாடு"},{"paragraph":"1. to be fond of honor"},{"paragraph":"2. to be ambitious"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English: </strong>Middle voice from a compound of <a href=\"#/G5384 - φίλος - phílos - fee'-los/5384\">G5384</a> and <a href=\"#/G5092 - τιμή - timḗ - tee-may'/5092\">G5092</a>; to be <i>fond of honor</i>, that is, <i>emulous</i> (<i>eager</i> or <i>earnest</i> to do somethng.): - labour, strive, study.</span>"},{"paragraph":""}]}